snippet.textDisplay: The biggest issue is the fact the UFC is a American business in its own right... it’s not been governed by an international organisation so to speak. So the judging system will be managed by local commissions depending on where the fight is taking place. This means some judges will have little to no experience in MMA. If this was a MMA world title fight and not a UFC title fight I would presume the scoring system would be accurate and scored properly for MMA and the judges would actually no what to score on. Having 4 rounds for Jones is a shocker. Shame as Reyes fought a great fight and deserved more.
